⚠️Check on sensitive groups
⚠️Do not leave children or pets in cars

Our nation's first responders - our police, EMT, and fire fighters - already work in dangerous and high stress jobs. #COVID19 compounds this.

My HERO Act would ensure first repsonders have access to mental health resources, especially during times of crisis like we are in now.

retweeted_text: Today, I’m proud to announce the #Taiwan Fellowship Act with @SenRubioPress, @RepTedYoho, and @RepBera. Our bipartisan/bicameral bill pushes back on China’s work to isolate the island nation diplomatically by placing ten U.S. fellows every year to live, study, and work in Taiwan.

full_text:
Last year, the Administration proposed a $15M cut to Defense programs that help prevent the next coronavirus.

On the floor of the House I reversed that cut and increased funding. This year, they are doing it again - but more so. I led a letter with 88 members to oppose it. https://t.co/Zzn3eiRXMA

But the fight for justice is far from over. We must recommit ourselves to ending systemic racism and inequality. https://t.co/KoqqXTcDHE

full_text:
Increased #COVID19 testing & contact tracing will allow states to loosen restrictions, but only with a vaccine will Americans be able to return to normal.

While I firmly believe the U.S. will be the first country to develop a vaccine, it’s possible that others may do so first.

full_text:
As a proud member of @CAPAC, I’m pleased to join my colleagues in celebrating Asian Pacific American Heritage Month.

This month we celebrate the rich history and diversity of our #AAPI community, and their significant contributions to American society.

full_text:
Wearing a cloth face covering correctly can help prevent the spread of #COVID19 to others.

When you go out on essential trips, follow these “do’s”. If you have a child, remember those under age 2 should not wear a face covering.

https://t.co/0v5dNQjwij https://t.co/1k0R3buJUM

Growing evidence suggests #COVID19 can spread before people show symptoms (pre-symptomatic) and from people who have #coronavirus but never show symptoms (asymptomatic). 
Cloth face coverings help prevent spread of COVID-19 in these situations.
See Q&A: https://t.co/vuYx19NZPE. https://t.co/RE9K3kZmYR

full_text:

That's why I joined my @NewDemCoalition colleagues in calling on the House to implement remote voting and virtual hearings.

https://t.co/R46o01Stj2 https://t.co/HX3WGtAjYA

full_text:
I applaud our state for leading the way on contact tracing.

In Congress, I'm leading the bipartisan effort to create a National Public Health Corps. We need a large and trained workforce to conduct the widespread testing necessary to re-open communities.

https://t.co/r3WoMJ6L5l https://t.co/Fel7tVQyXk

If we don’t keep one eye abroad, we unnecessarily leave our country at risk.

full_text:

All these risk factors around the world only increase the likelihood of #COVID19 reemerging in the United States.

full_text:
No matter how successful we are in fighting #COVID19 at home, we will never defeat it unless other parts of the world are equipped to prevent outbreaks from occurring and can contain them when they do occur.

Left unaddressed globally, #COVID19 will find its way back to the U.S.

The virus has hit the U.S. especially hard, with over 50,000 deaths and significant strain on our health systems.

Proud to join my colleagues in calling for the creation of a National Public Health Corps.

In order to start safely reopening communities, we need widespread contact tracing and serological testing. This testing requires a large, trained, and deployable workforce. #COVID19 https://t.co/zZ73lZJSWa

"A dedicated workforce is needed to rapidly deploy and fill multiple roles in the pandemic response that do not require formal medical training."

@SusanWBrooks and @RepBera call on the U.S. government to establish a Covid-19 Response Corps. https://t.co/I81o0klvZS

full_text:
That's why I'm urging Congress to include my HERO Act in future #COVID19 legislation. 

My bill would provide critical mental health resources to ensure our first responders are able to cope with the added stresses of completing their jobs during the #coronavirus pandemic. https://t.co/CfirtJaLhJ

full_text:
This results in a difficult dilemma: our nation’s firefighters, law enforcement, and EMTs confront the most stressful situations when they are on shift, and when they are off, now worry about infecting/exposing their loved ones at home.

The mental burdens they carry are immense.

And the stress imposed by the #coronavirus pandemic is only increasing those burdens.

full_text:

full_text:
I joined @RepBillFoster and @RepHoulahan in urging the Administration to prioritize the creation of a national testing strategy for #COVID19.

I led members of CA’s Congressional Delegation in urging @USDOL to issue guidance letting our state and others implement enhanced benefits to unemployed workers authorized by Congress.

Delays in getting this money out are unacceptable. Unemployed workers don’t have time to wait. https://t.co/st3H5Pm8E0

full_text:
.@GerryConnolly and I sent a letter to the Trump Administration in *2018* urging them not to abolish the global health security office, warning that their decision will "leave the U.S. vulnerable to pandemics."

We never received a response from the Administration. https://t.co/57W9HIKjPY

full_text:
Continue to stay inside, wash your hands, and stay safe. And please remember to check in on our seniors and most vulnerable populations. They need our love and support - now, more than ever.

Together we will get through this pandemic. We are a strong and resilient nation.

Communities count. 🏘️
Families count. 👨‍👨‍👧
We count. 👫🏾

Complete your #2020Census form online or via phone from the safety of your home. 📲 #EveryoneCounts

Follow @CACensus for more info. 
https://t.co/CHabD0nSo9

full_text: 📞 Spoke today with local gov't and chamber officials from Rancho Cordova, Elk Grove, and Carmichael. We discussed the latest on the #coronavirus and I briefed them on the economic relief that is coming to #CA07 through the #CARESAct. Look forward to continuing our conversations. https://t.co/gKF7hBokjt

Part of that process will be testing for COVID-19 antibodies to check to see if you’re immune. That’s why I joined @RepBillFoster @RepMoBrooks @RepBera bipartisan request for rapid deployment of coronavirus blood tests. https://t.co/bZfX2jy3Nl

Together, we will get through this pandemic.

#FlattenTheCurve #StayInformed

full_text:
This bipartisan legislation includes:

✅ $150 billion to State and local gov'ts
✅ $200 billion investment in hospitals
✅ $260 billion in unemployment benefits
✅ Immediate direct cash payments to lower and middle-income Americans
✅ More than $375 billion in small biz relief

I am proud to support this historic piece of legislation, which will bring urgent relief to American families and small businesses impacted by the #coronavirus.

Today’s vote is an important step in getting our communities back to health and on a path to economic recovery. https://t.co/WhLnMA9Prv
